&lt;p&gt;The problem is with your &lt;code&gt;$&lt;/code&gt; sign, and it is used to indicate the end of your expression. So basically, with that expression, you are looking for a string which ends with a 8 digit number. But in your second test string; &lt;code&gt;'236232 (82342450)'&lt;/code&gt;, ends with a bracket, and therefore it doesn't match the criteria (does not end with a number). &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;So remove the trailing &lt;code&gt;$&lt;/code&gt; and it will work.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code&gt;preg_match('/[0-9]{8}/',$string,$match);
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;

